#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530064
#; Severity: Feature
#; Category: Graphics
#; Symptom: Add PEI display and fix side effect.
#; RootCause:  1.FV size dosen't big enough when build debug binary with PEI display module
#; 2.The CrisisRecovery would do two times of PeiDisplayInit then the system hang.
#; Description: 1.Support Pei display on Release Binary.
#; 2.Fix the issue that CrisisRecovery hang when enable Pei display.
#; 3.The assert would happen when use debug binary to do the CrisisRecovery.
#; Solution:  1.Add IntelGraphicPeim when it's not building debug binary.
#; 2.Use XCMOS register 0x19 to prevent the PeiDisplayInit be done twice.
#; 3.Remove the assert which prevent TCO Base be set second time.
#; SolutionDependency: None

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530049
#; Severity: Tweak
#; Category: BDS
#; Symptom: After the MemoryTestFn() the Logo would be flushed.
#; RootCause: When MemoryTestFn() return EFI_NOT_FOUND cause the DisableQuietBoot() be executed.
#; Description: We return the EFI_NOT_FOUND status to prevent meaningless message be printed. It would cause the  DisableQuietBoot() be executed and the DisableQuietBoot() would flush the Logo.
#; Solution: Prevent the MemoryTestFn() print the meaningless and prevent the DisableQuietBoot() be executed. Break the while loop when it get the return status is EFI_NOT_FOUND.
#; SolutionDependency: IB16530030
#; Reviewer: IB16530000
#; RelatedFiles:

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530035
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: FormBrowser
#; Symptom: The exception happen at Front Page when use console redirection to remote PC
#; RootCause: FBNotifyEventToTarget try to find the Engine doesn't exist.
#; Description: FromBrowser not only use the "Event->Target(Console Id)" to recognize different node of the console out device, Console Redirection is Console In/Out device, but also use the "Event->Target(Console Id)" to determine the Engine(Text Mode Engine or Graphic Mode Engine), that cause the FBNotifyEventToTarget try to find the Engine doesn't exist.
#; Solution: Set FBNotifyEventToTarget use the first Engine on the EngineList,t determine to the value at H2O_FORM_BROWSER_TEXT_SUPPORT and H2O_FORM_BROWSER_METRO_SUPPORT at Project.env.If both of the H2O_FORM_BROWSER_TEXT_SUPPORT and H2O_FORM_BROWSER_METRO_SUPPORT at Project.env is "YES",EngineList[0] would choose the Text Mode as the ConsoleIn Engine,EngineList[1] would choose the Graphic Mode as the ConsoleIn Engine.
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB16530000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:
#;   1. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\BIOS_8M.7z
#;   2. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\GenFullBiosPackage.7z
#;   3. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\ObbLayout.exe
#;   4. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\bios.bin
#;   5. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\bios_APL_Ia32_RELEASE.bin
#;   6. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\bios_APL_X64_RELEASE.bin
#;   7. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\oemkeymn2.bin

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530033
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: SATA
#; Symptom: It would use more than 16 second to boot when enable Spin-up at Setup menu. (Advance>South Cluster.. >SATA Config>Spin Up Device)
#; RootCause: Current algorithm for staggered spin up command would check every port even though no device attached. For some AHCI controller, because BSY bit will never be cleared even though there's no device connect, this would led to a 16s timeout.
#; Description: Enable the SATA Spin Up cause the boot delay 16 second, update the AHCI driver to fix the issue.
#; Solution: Update Kernel 05.23.42 IB15850100 solution to fix.
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB16530000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:
#;   1. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\BIOS_8M.7z
#;   2. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\GenFullBiosPackage.7z
#;   3. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\ObbLayout.exe
#;   4. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\bios.bin
#;   5. ApolloLakeBoardPkg\Bios\bios_APL_Ia32_RELEASE.bin

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530032
#; Severity: Tweak
#; Category: RC
#; Symptom: SetupUtility Show the older version 1.1.0
#; RootCause: The PCD PcdIotgSiliconRefCodeVersion hadn't update

#; Issue#: IB16530030
#; Severity: Tweak
#; Category: MemoryTest
#; Symptom: Disable Queit/Quick Boot and the message "51% of the system memory tested OK" print
#; RootCause: It is the meaningless message in MemoryTestFn().
#; Description:Default setting doesn’t do the memory test and would return the EFI_NOT_FOUND let the code leave the while loop. It cause the MemoryTestFn() print the meaningless when it get the return status is EFI_NOT_FOUND.
#; Solution: When the staus is EFI_NOT_FOUND use "return status" to leave the while loop to prevent it print the meaningless message of memory test.
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB16530000

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0029
#; Issue#: IB16530028
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: Graphics
#; Symptom:Open the HotPlug feature in GOP cause the Text mode of front page and Setup Utility unstable 
#; RootCause: 
#; 1.Console Id of the layout node in H2ODisplayEngineLocalText.c isn't the serial number. It isn't unique and cause it would detach wrong node in the linklist.
#; 2.The node without device path could be build. Then front page may layout twice.
#; Description:1.When open the HotPlug feature and enable console redirection, Hot plug display port twice time at front page or Setup Utility. The exception happen.
#; 2.When open the HotPlug feature and disable console redirection, unplug the display port, then enter the front page. The front page chaotic. 
#; Solution: Renumbering the Console Id of the node when attach the node in H2ODisplayEngineLocalText.c and do not build the node without device path.
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB16530000

#; Tag#: 05.12.30.0019
#; Issue#: IB07400945
#; Severity: Feature
#; Category: MIPI-CSI/RC/Sync
#; Symptom: None
#; RootCause: None
#; Description: 1. Support MIPI-CSI camera device OV2740 and OV13858 on Oxbow Hill/Leaf Hill/Juniper Hill CRB.
#;                 Please configure Setup as blow to enable MIPI-CSI camera:
#;                   a. Advanced > Uncore Configuration > IPU Enable/Disable = <Enabled>
#;                   b. Advanced > Uncore Configuration > SA IPU ACPI mode   = <IGFX Child>
#;                   c. Advanced > Uncore Configuration > Rear Camera        = <IMX135(MD)/OV13858(I)>
#;                   d. Advanced > Uncore Configuration > Front Camera       = <OV2740>
#;              2. Integrated IUINT FW to support MIPI-CSI camera.
#;              3. Provide flag to switch SIC code version.

#; Tag#: 05.11.51.0015
#; Issue#: IB07400843
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: LPC/SIRQ/RMT
#; Symptom: None
#; RootCause: None
#; Description: 1. Refer "Comms Apollo Lake CeleronTM PentiumTM N, J series Feb 16" to do BIOS workaround.
#;                 a. Enable LPC CLKRUN# by setting LPC PCI offset E0h[0] to 1b. 
#;                    - Set SCU > Advanced > South Cluster Configuration > Misc Configuration > LPC Clock Run Pin = <Enabled>
#;                    - Changed default from <Disabled> to <Enabled> for this workaround.
#;                 b. Enable LPC PCE (Power Control Enable) by setting IOSF-SB port 0xD2 offset 0x341D bit3 and bit0 (SIC default)
#;                 c. Enable LPC CCE (Clock Control Enable) by setting IOSF-SB port 0xD2 offset 0x341C bits [3:0] (SIC default)
#;                 d. Set LPC SCNT (SERIRQ Control) Mode to Quiet Mode in LPC_CFG register, offset 0x64
#;                    - Set SCU > Advanced > South Cluster Configuration > Misc Configuration > Serial IRQ Mode = <Quiet Mode>
#;              2. Provide SIRQ enable and SIRQ mode setup option.
#;              3. Disable LPC CLKRUN# if build support for W8374LF LDC card.
#;              4. Fix uefi64rmt, uefi32rmt build fail issue.
#; Solution: None
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: None
